Resolves a chain (rollup/intent/leaf `.ctx` nodes) to actual file contents for display, treating missing files as soft `(absent: …)` markers rather than errors — only unreadable-but-present files produce `CtxError::Io`.

`parse_target` treats `"."` as repo root and trims a trailing `/` from directory targets before calling `RepoPath::parse`. `chain_for` decides file-vs-directory chain shape via `env.is_dir`, so callers passing a path to a file that doesn't exist yet will get treated as a file target through `chain::for_file`, not silently downgraded to a directory chain.

`fresh_chain_for(env, session_id, raw) -> Result<Option<Vec<ServedNode>>, CtxError>` is the session-deduplication entry point shared by hook mode and CLI mode: it loads the session's already-served node IDs via `session::load`, filters them out of the chain, and returns `None` if nothing *present* remains (absent markers alone don't count as "worth showing", even if they're new). On success it persists the updated served-set via `session::save` before returning — so a caller that gets `Some(nodes)` but then fails to display them still marks those nodes as shown for future calls; there's no rollback.

`render` produces the human-facing text with `=== id [kind] ===` section headers, ensuring each body ends with a trailing newline.

Depends on `chain.rs` for node-list construction and `session.rs` for the per-session served-set ledger; changes to `ChainNode`/`NodeKind` or to the session ledger's storage format require updating this file's usage in lockstep.